
/*
    BuildDefinition.json provides information to build your class library.

    1. Edit the template value for the build output of your liking.
       a. DotNetFramework - for .net framework projects.
       b. DotNetCore - for .net core projects.
       c. Documentation - future reference.

    2. Build Schemas identify the schemas in the database that should be built, as well as the namespace that schema will generate.
       a. Enter the database schema for SCHEMA, and the desired value for the NAMESPACE.
       b. Repeat the process for all schemas you wish to build.
       *Note that you can use the value + for the namespace to build directly into the project namespace.*

    3. Build Routines identify specific routines to be built in cases where an entire schema build is not desired.
       a. Enter the SCHEMA, NAMESPACE, and ROUTINE values.
       b. Repeat the process for all the routines you wish to build.
       *Note that you can use the value + for the namespace to build directly into the project namespace.*

    4. Remove any unnecessary BuildSchemas and BuildRoutines array items.

    5. Edit the EnumQueries
       a. Provide a name for the enumeration.
       b. Provide the source schema and table name.
       c. Provide the table column for the enumeration string constant
       d. Provide the table column for the enumeration value
       e. Provide an optional filter.

    6. Remove any unnecessary EnumQueries array items.

    7. Edit the StaticQueries
       a. Provide the name for the static data.
       b. Provide the query for the static data.

    8. Save and close the file.
    
  
    For additional information for setting up your project build vist www.SQLPLUS.net

    You may delete these comments if you like.
*/

{
  "Template": "DotNetCore",
  "BuildSchemas": [
    {
      "Schema": "dbo",
      "Namespace": "+"
    }
  ]
}
